** _ Glencore Australia have a number of opportunities opening to graduating or recently graduated university students to join our Graduate Program commencing in February 2025. As a valued member of our team, you will play a crucial role in a global organisation that is committed to your success. Join us on this exciting journey and make a meaningful impact on your professional development. _ **

** About Us **

As a key player in Australias mining landscape, Glencore spans across 23 mine
sites, responsibly sourcing commodities that advance everyday life. From the
copper, cobalt and nickel powering the electric vehicle revolution, and the
energy products like coal to help keep the lights on, what Glencore does
touches every part of life. Our portfolio enables the transition to a low-
carbon economy, while meeting society’s energy needs. Beyond our extensive
portfolio, Glencore offers unparalleled career and development opportunities,
fostering strong communities. Join Glencore to be part of a team shaping a
future where your contributions matter.

** About the Role **

As a Graduate Information Systems and Technology Professional, you will be
exposed to various duties undertaken in the Business Systems, Networks and
Infrastructure. Over the course of the program you’ll be shown the ropes by
our various teams, then depending on your skillset you’ll be off doing project
work – it could be software development, or organisational change management,
business analysis or infrastructure support if that’s what your skills are
aligned to. No matter which might be, you will assist with experienced IS&T
team to create right setup technologically and make a positive difference for
optimal business performance across our mine sites.

As a Glencore graduate, you’ll have access to unrivalled opportunities and
unlimited potential to grow your career. This is your opportunity to test your
skills and creativity in real situations! With over 50 IS&T professionals in
your team, you will be working with some of the best in the fields of
telecommunication, systems engineering, application development, systems
analysts, and IS&T support. Graduates will be provided with an exciting place
to grow and develop during the early stage of their careers, often receiving
projects very early in their placements. You will have the opportunity to work
with leaders in your field in the following locations:

  * _ Mount Isa, QLD (Residential) _
  * _ Townsville, QLD (Residential) _

** About You **

  * Qualified with a Bachelor of Computer Science, Bachelor of Information Technology, Bachelor of Information Systems or similar (prior to commencement) 
  * Committed to maintaining a safe work environment 
  * Exhibit an openness and willingness to learn 

** The Perks **

  * Competitive remuneration inclusive of allowances 
  * Be part of a structured Graduate Professional Development Program designed to accelerate your leadership potential 
  * Attend scheduled networking and social events with other graduates and members of the senior management teams 
  * Receive mentorship from leading industry professionals, guiding you towards becoming a future leader within the business 
  * Access to Glencore Rewards, our online discount platform with 100s of retailers – including Apple, Airbnb, and other retailers 

Applications will be accepted via www.glencore.com/careers and close 14 April
2024.  
Please note: separate applications for Coal and Zinc assets are required.

Job Search Reference Number: ** GRAD2025IST **

